</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p "> Make sure the correct media thickness is entered in the profile and use the correct profile. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Maintain printer according to the care/use poster. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">Ink needs to spread evenly over the top layer of the media to give a smooth appearance. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The most important parameter which influences the visibility of graininess is the distance between the printheads and the surface of the media. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Due to a mismatch of the distance the droplets might end on different locations on the media than expected. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Parameters that determine spreading are: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Amount of ink : 
</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When the droplets are too small the ink volume to cover the top layer of the media is too less and therefor graininess is more sensitive at lower coverage. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Distance to spread : 
</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When the droplets are positioned on top of each other instead of next to each other, the distance to cover by spreading increases. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The distance of the printheads to the surface of the media is the parameter which can influence this aspect. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Time to spread : 
</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The print mode determines the time between landing of droplet and curing of the ink. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">At gloss mode the ink has more time to spread compared to Matt-modes. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Therefor graininess is more sensitive at Matt-modes. 
</p></li></ul></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-945E6C60-1212-47DF-9487-92374227D4B4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
